<br>
On the health issue, resistant Tuberculosis epidemic shows what happens if your stupid enough to NOT have non-commerical health care as your primary health system.  Disease doesnt give a damn if your rich or poor, anyone ever studied history, cholera and plague epidemics of middle ages and the 1800s?<br>
Commercial health care doesnt have an interest in CURING DISEASE OR PREVENTING IT. becuse that chokes the cash flow. At the end of the day, the only goal is to make cash, not cure. Hippocratic Oath, anyone? Scandals of not accepting high cost patients, selling treatments at vastly inflated prices...<br>
  People should have the right to CHOSE their doctor, but *nobody* should *EVER* be able to *BUY* better health care than someone else, except when it's purely cosmetic surgery (which is usally a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>want</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, not a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>need</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->).<br>
<br>
2 peopel, dying of same condition, rich one pays huge money to get the surgery first, other one dies. Anyone see the moral problems with this, hm?<br>
<br>
These are basic moral questions. Being right wing doesnt mean your ideas are any more or less valid than left wing, but it's the basic MORALITY of it all that's important. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=magisarabeth>MagiSarabeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#333333>(10/25/02 6:45:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=364.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: idiot socialists</span><hr size=1> Different people have different ideas of what is moral, too.<br>
The left wing defines morality as the government forcing me to pay for health, education, etc for others I don't even know. The right wing tends to accept that I can choose to do this for myself for those I feel are worthy.<br>
<br>
The &quot;Poor&quot; in America are better off than people in less capitalistic societies. (VCRs, cars, other things people would call luxuries in a less rich society) I fail to see the Great Enemy of Capitalism that you do.<br>
<br>
People die. That's life. Rich or poor, etc. <br>
Oh and life isn't fair. It isn't going to be. And no law can make it so either.<br>
<br>
That transplant you talk about -- how would you determine who gets it if not who can afford to pay for it themselves? Do you know about the public health program in canada and how many people come to the US to get help before they die because of the waiting periods, etc?<br>
<br>
You probably think me heartless because I DO accept that death is part of life. That everyone can't have everything they want or desire. Andthat even the rich have their problems. (BTW what do you define as rich? Someone able to afford a transplant? Do you have any idea how many transplants are paid for by the community -- NOT the government forced community , but voluntarily, people getting together to give to a cause. Churches taking up special offerings for those active in their bodies, etc. Forcing people to be part of (a material part of) their community for that added bit of insurance later on.<br>
<br>
It isn't a bad thing to expect people to take care of each other -- those they care for, etc. It makes sure money isn't wasted on those who don't have true needs. And helps those who donate to KNOW that their money is being spent wisely and to see the results for themselves.<br>
<br>
