<br>
The heart of socialism is very simple actually, its all about mankind: man must be the center of everything, it has to be the subject of his own future, not an object in a theory where welth creation would be the main concern (aka capitalism).<br>
<br>
Very simply, what are we talking about here?<br>
<br>
Social Justice, same Education for everyone, minimal housing and clothing guaranteed.<br>
<br>
Guarantee that everyone in the country will have the same access to those very basic needs, for the same price and at a very high quality : Energy, transports, education, Health system, Communications, ...<br>
<br>
This is called public utilities.<br>
<br>
The principles are easy to grasp: the private sphere must interfere the least possible, if you decide to work for your people, fine, but you will be at their service, the particularity beeing that you cant make benefits from such activity, nor demand any form of profitability except the general well beeing.<br>
<br>
It means of course that the state must be very strong, but why wouldnt it be the case, since its the manifestation of the Nation will?<br>
